In physics, the generalized coordinates for a Hamiltonian system with associated Hamiltonian function 
  
    
      
        
          
            H
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\mathcal {H}}}
  , consisting of space coordinates 
  
    
      
        
          
            q
          
          
            i
          
        
        (
        t
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {q} _{i}(t)}
   and momenta 
  
    
      
        
          
            p
          
          
            i
          
        
        (
        t
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {p} _{i}(t)}
  , are called action angle coordinates if the Hamiltonian function depends only on the momenta 
  
    
      
        
          
            p
          
          
            i
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {p} _{i}}
  , and not on the position 
  
    
      
        
          
            q
          
          
            i
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle \mathbf {q} _{i}}
  . In action angle coordinates, Hamilton's equations take on the form:

  
    
      
        
          
            
              ∂
              
                
                  p
                
                
                  i
                
              
            
            
              ∂
              t
            
          
        
        =
        0
        
        ,
        
        
          
            
              ∂
              
                
                  q
                
                
                  i
                
              
            
            
              ∂
              t
            
          
        
        =
        
          
            
              ∂
              
                
                  H
                
              
            
            
              ∂
              
                
                  p
                
                
                  i
                
              
            
          
        
      
    
    {\displaystyle {\frac {\partial \mathbf {p} _{i}}{\partial t}}=0\,,\quad {\frac {\partial \mathbf {q} _{i}}{\partial t}}={\frac {\partial {\mathcal {H}}}{\partial \mathbf {p} _{i}}}}
